FBIS4-51842 "dreas086_j_94003" FBIS-EAS-94-086 Daily Report 30 Apr 1994 SOUTHEAST ASIA Indonesia Indonesian Ambassador on Refugees' Repatriation Indonesian Ambassador on Refugees' Repatriation BK3004092894 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in Indonesian 0000 GMT 30 Apr 94 BK3004092894 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network Indonesian BFN [Text] Vietnamese refugees who are currently staying on Galang Island in Riau will be gradually repatriated by the end of next year. Indonesian Ambassador to Vietnam Jaafar Hussein Assegaf said the repatriation of the Vietnamese refugees is related to Indonesia's plan to turn Galang Island into an economic and industrial center. An estimated 8,000 Vietnamese refugees are currently staying on Galang Island.
